The first Speaker of Plateau State House of Assembly, Prof. Dakum Shown has died at the age of 74 after protracted illness. The announcement of his death was contained in a statement signed by the Director of Press and Public Affairs to Governor Simon Lalong, Dr. Makut Simon Macham. Prof. Shown, an academic and politician, was the first Speaker of Plateau State House of Assembly who served in the Second Republic from 1979 to 1983 during the administration of Chief Solomon Daushep Lar, and was also Plateau State PDP Chairman from 2009 to 2011. He was the first Nigerian Principal of the famous Girls High School, Gindiri (GHS) and one-time chairman of National Institute for Policy and Strategic Studies (NIPSS). Plateau State governor Simon Lalong described Prof. Shown as “An honest, patriotic, fearless, and competent person.” LG autonomy: Plateau, Taraba, Katsina teachers protest Dalung, Dariye, 47 others make Lalong’s re-election campaign council Group wants Lalong to support Maje’s ambition for speaker